<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Musicians such as Taylor Swift, Billie Eilish and Cher are donating some of their most iconic items to benefit the MuisCares charity.</p>

<p>Julien's Auctions announced the items that will go on the auction block at their MusiCares Foundation Charity Auction, which takes place Wednesday, September 9.</p>

<p>Advanced online bidding is already under way at JuliensAuctions.com, with the items available to be viewed by the public next week.</p>

<p>Auction: Musicians such as Taylor Swift, Billie Eilish and Cher are donating some of their most iconic items to benefit the MuisCares charity</p>

<p>Taylor Swift's contribution is a signed Gibson American Eagle LG-2 acoustic guitar, which is expected to sell for between $2,000 and $3,000.</p>

<p>Billie Eilish is putting up a signed Fender California Coast black ukulele with yellow abstract pattern, which is projected to fetch between $2,000 and $4,000.</p>

<p>Cher is putting on the block a custom black and silver jacket with crystal and stone designs, with a custom microphone pouch, estimated to sell between $4,000 and $6,000.</p>

<p>Taylor's guitar: Taylor Swift's contribution is a signed Gibson American Eagle LG-2 acoustic guitar, which is expected to sell for between $2,000 and $3,000</p>

<p>Custom: Billie Eilish is putting up a signed Fender California Coast black ukulele with yellow abstract pattern, which is projected to fetch between $2,000 and $4,000</p>

<p>Cher's jacket: Cher is putting on the block a custom black and silver jacket with crystal and stone designs, with a custom microphone pouch, estimated to sell between $4,000 and $6,000</p>

<p>Other big-ticket items include a Gucci metallic blue tracksuit owned and worn by Elton John, expected to fetch between $4,000 and $6,000.</p>

<p>One of the few items from the sports world is a basketball signed by NBA superstars Bill Russell, Larry Bird, Dennis Johnson, Tom “Satch” Sanders, Don Nelson, Tom Heinsohn, Frank Ramsey, Ed Macauley, Bill Sharman, Cedric Maxwell, Nate Archibald, JoJo White, and Sam Jones, donated by Rick Fox, estimated to sell for between $4,000 and $6,000.</p>

<p>TV fans will get to bid on ablack leather jacket worn by John Stamos in Full House accompanied by a handwritten postcard by Stamos, where he says it's his 'favorite leather jacket, but anything for MusiCares,' </p>

<p>Elton's tracksuit: Other big-ticket items include a Gucci metallic blue tracksuit owned and worn by Elton John, expected to fetch between $4,000 and $6,000</p>

<p>Basketball: One of the few items from the sports world is a basketball signed by NBA superstars Bill Russell, Larry Bird, Dennis Johnson, Tom “Satch” Sanders, Don Nelson, Tom Heinsohn, Frank Ramsey, Ed Macauley, Bill Sharman, Cedric Maxwell, Nate Archibald, JoJo White, and Sam Jones, donated by Rick Fox, estimated to sell for between $4,000 and $6,000</p>

<p>Another Full House item is a 1989 script signed by Stamos and other cast members, expected to sell between $2,000 and $3,00.  </p>

<p>Barbra Streissand also donated a caftan dress she wore in the 2004 film Meet the Fockers, which is estimated to sell between $3,000 and $5,000.</p>

<p>Crooner Tom Jones donated a custom black velvet bomber jacket with 'Tom' embroidered in gold, a red dragon and a feathered crown that reads “Ich Dien” on the back, believed to sell between $4,000-$6,000.</p>

<p>Barbra's caftan: Barbra Streissand also donated a caftan dress she wore in the 2004 film Meet the Fockers, which is estimated to sell between $3,000 and $5,000</p>

<p>Tom's jacket: Crooner Tom Jones donated a custom black velvet bomber jacket with 'Tom' embroidered in gold, a red dragon and a feathered crown that reads “Ich Dien” on the back, believed to sell between $4,000-$6,000</p>

<p>Other items include a signed guitar from One Direction's Harry Styles, along with a custom outfit worn by Ozzy Osborne, expected to fetch between $6,000 and $8,000.</p>

<p>Fans can also bid on Dave Gahan’s metallic silver blazer stage worn while performing with Depeche Mode throughout the band’s 2013 tour (estimate: $3,000-$5,000). </p>

<p>Also up for auction is an orange silk Mariko jacket worn by Carole King as part of her disguise when she went incognito to watch her Broadway play (estimate: $3,000-$5,000).</p>

<p>Fans will be able to see all of these items in a public exhibition at Julien's Auctions Beverly Hills (257 N. Canon Drive, Beverly Hills, CA 90210) daily between Monday, September 7 and Friday, September 11 from 11 AM to 5 PM, with admission free to the public.  </p>

